Oy | Facilities | 61.74 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 377 | Work Easy Space Solutions Private Limited | Facilities | 14,913.21 | Managed office and co-working spaces in India | Terminate |\n| 378 | Workato, Inc. | Engineering | 16,101.03 | Enterprise automation and integration platform | Consolidate |\n| 379 | Xenon Savjetovanje D.O.O. | Facilities | 164.02 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 380 | Yellow Submarine D.O.O. | Facilities | 486.21 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 381 | Yoxel, Inc | Engineering | 2,043.60 | API integration and data synchronization services | Terminate |\n| 382 | Zagrebacki Holding D.O.O. | Facilities | 142.83 | Croatian local vendor providing miscellaneous services | Terminate |\n| 383 | Zagrebtower D.O.O. | Facilities | 183,754.42 | Zagreb Tower office premises rent and services | Optimize |\n| 384 | Zapier Inc. | Engineering | 166.79 | Workflow automation and app integration platform | Consolidate |\n| 385 | Zettanet | Engineering | 183.37 | Network management and connectivity services | Consolidate |\n| 386 | Zivi Napitak D.O.O. | Facilities | 3,699.58 | Food, beverage or hospitality services for office | Terminate |\n| 387 | Zuric I Partneri Odvjetnicko Drustvo D.O.O. | Legal | 24,135.44 | Croatian law firm for corporate and commercial law | Terminate |\n\nRows 388 onward are blank.\n\n---\n\n## === TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES ===\n\n**Headers (Row 1):** `[blank] | Opportunity | Explanation | Estimated Annual Savings (USD)`\n\n**A1 raw:** `undefined` (cell A1 is empty)\n\n| Row | Label | Opportunity | Explanation | Est. Savings (USD) |\n|-----|-------|-------------|-------------|-------------------|\n| 2 | Opportunity 1 | Renegotiate Salesforce UK Enterprise Contract | Salesforce at $3.1M is 39.5% of total vendor spend (Parallel Strategic). Right-size unused licences and renegotiate multi-year enterprise pricing tiers. 15% reduction delivers $468K annually; renewal window is critical leverage. | 467,584 |\n| 3 | Opportunity 2 | Execute Long-tail Vendor Termination Program | 267 Terminate-rated vendors hold $1.6M in redundant spend (Immediate). Cancel Score-1 SaaS subscriptions first; issue notices for contract vendors. 10% realisation in 90 days yields $163K with minimal operational risk. | 163,215 |\n| 4 | Opportunity 3 | Consolidate Co-working and Office Space Portfolio | $828K fragmented across 8 co-working vendors; high duplication (Parallel Strategic). Consolidate to 1–2 preferred operators; renegotiate volume-based pricing. 15% reduction through preferred-operator terms saves $124K annually. | 124,175 |\n\nRows 5–7 are blank.\n\n---\n\n## === CEOCFO RECOMMENDATIONS ===\n\n**A1 raw (instruction text):**\n> \"Please prepare a short memo (maximum 1 page) summarizing your findings and recommendations to the CEO and CFO. Please keep in mind that these are busy people; position your points accordingly, focus on what really matters, and do not exceed the number of pages; do not overemphasize things that are obvious to them but also keep in mind they have many things going on and may not remember immediately certain points. Please provide a Google Doc link to your memo below\"\n\n**A2 raw (hyperlink):**\n- Display text: `CEOCFORecommendations`\n- Link target: `https://docs.google.com/document/d/1uiPtEcUOMAoGUtS6nV_j5IXhJj1QKtN47ZlylTcu32I/edit?usp=sharing`\n\n**A3 raw (full memo text):**\n\n```\nMEMORANDUM\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Strategic Procurement Lead\nDATE: 22 March 2026\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\n\n1. VENDOR SPEND OVERVIEW\n- 386 active vendors | Total LTM spend: $7,887,360\n- Breakdown: 265 vendors for Termination ($1,475,052, 18.7%); 22 for Optimisation ($4,899,490, 62.1%); 99 for Consolidation ($1,512,819, 19.2%)\n- Top 10 vendors account for 63.9% of total spend — acute concentration risk\n\n3. TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES\n- Opportunities structured across Immediate and Parallel Strategic tracks to maximise speed, feasibility, and minimise operational risk\n- Execute Long-tail Vendor Termination Program (Immediate): cancel 265 low-value SaaS subscriptions; issue non-renewal notices for tail contracts — est. $163,215\n- Renegotiate Salesforce UK Enterprise Contract (Parallel Strategic): right-size unused licences and renegotiate multi-year pricing using $3.1M volume leverage — est. $467,584\n- Consolidate Co-working and Office Space Portfolio (Parallel Strategic): consolidate 8 co-working vendors to 1–2 preferred operators; renegotiate volume-based terms — est. $124,175\nTotal estimated savings: $755,000\n\n4. ESTIMATED SAVINGS SUMMARY\n- Total identified savings: $755,000 (9.6% of total LTM spend)\n- Year 1 conservatively realisable: $453,000 (60% of identified savings)\n- Payback on implementation effort: under 6 months\n\n5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP\n- Month 1–2: Execute immediate termination actions; initiate strategic renegotiation in parallel\n- Month 3–4: Continue consolidation; advance strategic negotiations\n- Month 4–6: Complete strategic initiatives and embed controls\n- Month 6+: Embed vendor governance, enforce controls, and prevent spend creep\n\n6. RISKS AND MITIGATIONS\n- Service disruption from vendor exits: stagger terminations; confirm substitutes before exit\n- Salesforce negotiation failure: engage pre-renewal; deploy $3.1M volume leverage early\n- Vendor concentration risk: run parallel CRM benchmark if Salesforce talks stall\n\nRecommended next step: CPO to engage Salesforce UK in Q2 2026 ahead of enterprise renewal, leveraging $3.1M volume to target a minimum 15% reduction ($468K annually); in parallel, Procurement to initiate the 265-vendor termination program in Month 1 to deliver $163K in immediate savings.\n```\n\n---\n\n**Summary of key findings across the three sheets:**\n\n- **Vendor Analysis Assessment**: 386 vendors with columns for Vendor Name, Department, LTM Cost (USD), 1-line Description, and Suggestion (Consolidate/Terminate/Optimize). Data runs rows 2–387; rows 388+ are blank.\n- **Top 3 Opportunities**: 3 opportunities with estimated savings of $467,584 / $163,215 / $124,175 (total $754,974). Cell A1 is empty (the column header area starts at B1).\n- **CEOCFO Recommendations**: A1 = instruction prompt text; A2 = hyperlink cell displaying \"CEOCFORecommendations\" linking to `https://docs.google.com/document/d/1uiPtEcUOMAoGUtS6nV_j5IXhJj1QKtN47ZlylTcu32I/edit?usp=sharing`; A3 = full memo content (dated 22 March 2026, covering spend overview, top 3 opportunities, savings summary, implementation roadmap, and risks/mitigations)."}],"totalDurationMs":347998,"totalTokens":61139,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8264,"cache_read_input_tokens":37029,"output_tokens":15845,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8264},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
