{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014XmVfwTYPpBosDH771zkDW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete output from the script:\n\n---\n\n**=== VENDOR ANALYSIS ASSESSMENT SUMMARY ===**\n\n- Total vendors: 386 | Total spend: $7,887,360.40\n- Terminate: 265 vendors | Spend: $1,475,051.79 | 18.7%\n- Optimize: 0 vendors | Spend: $0.00 | 0.0%\n- Consolidate: 99 vendors | Spend: $1,512,818.99 | 19.2%\n- Top 10 spend: $5,042,189.13 | 63.9% of total\n\n**Top 10 Vendors by Spend:**\n1. Salesforce Uk Ltd-Uk — $3,117,225.89\n2. Navan (Tripactions Inc) — $357,983.62\n3. Bdo Llp — $343,081.39\n4. Tog Uk Properties Limited — $263,821.16\n5. Cloudcrossing Bvba — $208,675.15\n6. Zagrebtower D.O.O. — $183,754.42\n7. Innovent Spaces Private Limited — $147,347.80\n8. Weking D.O.O. — $144,093.20\n9. Jensten Insurance Brokers — $142,699.73\n10. Gpt Space & Co — $133,506.78\n\n---\n\n**=== TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES - ALL CELLS ===**\n\n| | Opportunity | Explanation | Est. Annual Savings (USD) |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Opp 1 | Renegotiate Salesforce UK Enterprise Contract | $3.1M is 39.5% of total spend; right-size unused licences + multi-year pricing; 15% reduction = $468K | $467,584 |\n| Opp 2 | Execute Long-tail Vendor Termination Program | 267 Terminate-rated vendors hold $1.6M; cancel Score-1 SaaS first; 10% in 90 days = $163K | $163,215 |\n| Opp 3 | Consolidate Co-working and Office Space Portfolio | $828K across 8 vendors; consolidate to 1–2 preferred operators; 15% reduction = $124K | $124,175 |\n\n---\n\n**=== CEOCFO RECOMMENDATIONS - CELLS A1, A2, A3 ===**\n\n- **A1:** Contains the worksheet instruction (max 1-page memo to CEO/CFO + Google Doc link required)\n- **A2:** `\"CEOCFORecommendations\"` (label/header)\n- **A3:** Full memo text — MEMORANDUM to CEO/CFO from R. Jegadeswari dated 22 March 2026, covering: vendor spend overview (386 vendors, $7.89M LTM), top 3 opportunities ($755K total identified savings, $453K Year 1 realisable), implementation roadmap (Month 1–6), risks/mitigations, and recommended next step (Salesforce renegotiation in Q2 2026 + parallel 265-vendor termination program)\n- **B1, B2, C1:** All empty"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2c3d7c3f62a5bd68 (use SendMessage with to: 'a2c3d7c3f62a5bd68' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 12916\ntool_uses: 1\nduration_ms: 20082</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2abd3ed-573c-41f0-9505-cb2e0fcd9d65","uuid":"a99c3cda-48d8-46c4-9d34-34590a95d733","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:51:09.687Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read specific data from the Excel workbook at C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\n\nRun this Node.js script to get ONLY the key data I need:\n\n```javascript\nconst XLSX = require('xlsx');\nconst path = 'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx';\nconst wb = XLSX.readFile(path);\n\n// 1. Summarize Vendor Analysis Assessment - counts and totals by suggestion\nconsole.log('=== VENDOR ANALYSIS ASSESSMENT SUMMARY ===');\nconst vaa = wb.Sheets['Vendor Analysis Assessment'];\nconst vaaData = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(vaa, {defval: ''});\nlet terminate = {count: 0, spend: 0};\nlet optimize = {count: 0, spend: 0};\nlet consolidate = {count: 0, spend: 0};\nlet total = {count: 0, spend: 0};\nvaaData.forEach(row => {\n  const cost = parseFloat(row['Last 12 months Cost (USD)']) || 0;\n  const suggestion = (row['Suggestions (Consolidate / Terminate / Optimize costs)'] || '').trim();\n  total.count++;\n  total.spend += cost;\n  if (suggestion === 'Terminate') { terminate.count++; terminate.spend += cost; }\n  else if (suggestion === 'Optimize costs') { optimize.count++; optimize.spend += cost; }\n  else if (suggestion === 'Consolidate') { consolidate.count++; consolidate.spend += cost; }\n});\nconsole.log('Total vendors:', total.count, '| Total spend:', total.spend.toFixed(2));\nconsole.log('Terminate:', terminate.count, '| Spend:', terminate.spend.toFixed(2), '|', (terminate.spend/total.spend*100).toFixed(1)+'%');\nconsole.log('Optimize:', optimize.count, '| Spend:', optimize.spend.toFixed(2), '|', (optimize.spend/total.spend*100).toFixed(1)+'%');\nconsole.log('Consolidate:', consolidate.count, '| Spend:', consolidate.spend.toFixed(2), '|', (consolidate.spend/total.spend*100).toFixed(1)+'%');\n\n// Top 10 spend\nconst sorted = vaaData.sort((a,b) => (parseFloat(b['Last 12 months Cost (USD)'])||0) - (parseFloat(a['Last 12 months Cost (USD)'])||0));\nconst top10Spend = sorted.slice(0,10).reduce((s,r) => s + (parseFloat(r['Last 12 months Cost (USD)'])||0), 0);\nconsole.log('Top 10 spend:', top10Spend.toFixed(2), '|', (top10Spend/total.spend*100).toFixed(1)+'%');\nconsole.log('Top 10 vendors:');\nsorted.slice(0,10).forEach((r,i) => console.log(i+1, r['Vendor Name'], '$'+parseFloat(r['Last 12 months Cost (USD)']).toFixed(2)));\n\n// 2. Read Top 3 Opportunities sheet - ALL cells\nconsole.log('\\n=== TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES - ALL CELLS ===');\nconst t3 = wb.Sheets['Top 3 Opportunities'];\nconst range = XLSX.utils.decode_range(t3['!ref']);\nfor (let r = range.s.r; r <= range.e.r; r++) {\n  for (let c = range.s.c; c <= range.e.c; c++) {\n    const addr = XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r,c});\n    if (t3[addr]) console.log(addr+':', JSON.stringify(t3[addr].v));\n  }\n}\n\n// 3. Read CEOCFO Recommendations - key cells\nconsole.log('\\n=== CEOCFO RECOMMENDATIONS - CELLS A1, A2, A3 ===');\nconst ceo = wb.Sheets['CEOCFO Recommendations'];\n['A1','A2','A3','B1','B2','C1'].forEach(cell => {\n  if (ceo[cell]) console.log(cell+':', JSON.stringify(ceo[cell].v));\n  else console.log(cell+': (empty)');\n});\n```\n\nRun with: node script.js from C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/\n\nReturn the complete output.","agentId":"a2c3d7c3f62a5bd68","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the complete output from the script:\n\n-