{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AA9ojZuwJMMJXk9Ubr9xqc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The script ran successfully. Here is the complete output:\n\n```\nA1 exists: true\nA2 exists: true\nA1 value preview: Please prepare a short memo (maximum 1 page) summarizing your findings and recom\nA2 value: CEOCFORecommendations\nWriting to cell: A3\nDone. File saved.\n\nVerification:\nA1 still exists: true\nA2 still: CEOCFORecommendations\nA3 first 200 chars: MEMORANDUM\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Procurement & Finance\nDATE: 23 March 2026\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\n\n1. VENDO\n```\n\nKey results:\n\n- A1 and A2 were untouched — A1 holds the template instruction text, A2 holds the label \"CEOCFORecommendations\".\n- `XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r: 2, c: 0})` correctly resolved to `A3`.\n- The full memo was written to A3 and verified on re-read, with the opening 200 characters confirming the correct content starts with \"MEMORANDUM\\nTO: Chief Executive Officer...\".\n- The workbook was saved back to `/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a454257785fed0dc5 (use SendMessage with to: 'a454257785fed0dc5' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 17322\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 56781</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2abd3ed-573c-41f0-9505-cb2e0fcd9d65","uuid":"9f47f16d-cc15-46e0-b62c-1c3b0f02b725","timestamp":"2026-03-22T18:54:12.635Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Write a Node.js script and run it to write a memo to cell A3 of the \"CEOCFO Recommendations\" sheet in the workbook at:\nC:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\n\nCRITICAL CONSTRAINTS:\n- Do NOT overwrite A1 or A2 — they already contain template instructions and a label\n- Write ONLY to cell A3\n- Use XLSX.utils.encode_cell to target A3\n- Do NOT use aoa_to_sheet or any method that rebuilds the sheet\n- Read the file, modify only A3, then write back\n\nHere is the exact memo text to write to A3 (use \\n for line breaks, \\n\\n between major sections):\n\n```\nMEMORANDUM\\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Procurement & Finance\\nDATE: 23 March 2026\\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\\n\\n1. VENDOR SPEND OVERVIEW\\n- 386 active vendors | Total LTM spend: $7.89M\\n- Breakdown: 265 vendors for Termination ($1.48M, 18.7%); 22 for Optimisation ($4.90M, 62.1%); 99 for Consolidation ($1.51M, 19.2%)\\n- Top 10 vendors account for 63.9% of total spend — acute concentration risk\\n\\n3. TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES\\n- Opportunities structured across Immediate and Parallel Strategic tracks to maximise speed, feasibility, and minimise operational risk\\n- Salesforce UK Contract Renegotiation (Immediate): right-size licences and secure multi-year pricing — est. $467,584\\n- Long-tail Vendor Termination Program (Parallel Strategic): cancel 265 Terminate-rated vendors, prioritising Score-1 SaaS first — est. $163,215\\n- Co-working & Office Space Consolidation: rationalise 8 vendors ($828K portfolio) to 1–2 preferred operators — est. $124,175\\nTotal estimated savings: $754,974\\n\\n4. ESTIMATED SAVINGS SUMMARY\\n- Total identified savings: $754,974 (9.6% of total LTM spend)\\n- Year 1 conservatively realisable: $453,000 (60% of identified savings)\\n- Payback on implementation effort: under 6 months\\n\\n5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP\\n- Month 1–2: Launch Salesforce renegotiation with procurement lead; activate 265-vendor termination program targeting Score-1 SaaS cancellations first\\n- Month 3–4: Continue vendor termination closures; issue co-working RFP and consolidate 8 operators to preferred panel of 1–2\\n- Month 4–6: Execute final Salesforce contract amendment; complete co-working consolidation and migrate headcount to retained locations\\n- Month 6+: Institutionalise quarterly vendor governance reviews; enforce category ownership to prevent tail-spend creep\\n\\n6. RISKS AND MITIGATIONS\\n- Salesforce service disruption: Negotiate phased licence reduction with no-downtime SLA protection\\n- Departmental resistance to terminations: Engage budget owners early to pre-empt escalations\\n- Co-working lease break penalties: Review break clauses before issuing termination notices\\n\\nRecommended next step: Assign procurement lead to initiate Salesforce UK renegotiation by 30 April 2026, while simultaneously activating the 265-vendor termination program in Week 1 to capture quick-win savings in parallel.\n```\n\nWrite and run this script:\n\n```javascript\nconst XLSX = require('xlsx');\nconst filePath = 'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx';\n\nconst wb = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\nconst sheetName = 'CEOCFO Recommendations';\nconst ws = wb.Sheets[sheetName];\n\n// Verify A1 and A2 are present (do not overwrite)\nconsole.log('A1 exists:', !!ws['A1']);\nconsole.log('A2 exists:', !!ws['A2']);\nconsole.log('A1 value preview:', ws['A1'] ? ws['A1'].v.substring(0, 80) : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A2 value:', ws['A2'] ? ws['A2'].v : '(empty)');\n\n// Write only to A3\nconst memoText = \"MEMORANDUM\\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Procurement & Finance\\nDATE: 23 March 2026\\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\\n\\n1. VENDOR SPEND OVERVIEW\\n- 386 active vendors | Total LTM spend: $7.89M\\n- Breakdown: 265 vendors for Termination ($1.48M, 18.7%); 22 for Optimisation ($4.90M, 62.1%); 99 for Consolidation ($1.51M, 19.2%)\\n- Top 10 vendors account for 63.9% of total spend — acute concentration risk\\n\\n3. TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES\\n- Opportunities structured across Immediate and Parallel Strategic tracks to maximise speed, feasibility, and minimise operational risk\\n- Salesforce UK Contract Renegotiation (Immediate): right-size licences and secure multi-year pricing — est. $467,584\\n- Long-tail Vendor Termination Program (Parallel Strategic): cancel 265 Terminate-rated vendors, prioritising Score-1 SaaS first — est. $163,215\\n- Co-working & Office Space Consolidation: rationalise 8 vendors ($828K portfolio) to 1\\u20132 preferred operators — est. $124,175\\nTotal estimated savings: $754,974\\n\\n4. ESTIMATED SAVINGS SUMMARY\\n- Total identified savings: $754,974 (9.6% of total LTM spend)\\n- Year 1 conservatively realisable: $453,000 (60% of identified savings)\\n- Payback on implementation effort: under 6 months\\n\\n5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP\\n- Month 1\\u20132: Launch Salesforce renegotiation with procurement lead; activate 265-vendor termination program targeting Score-1 SaaS cancellations first\\n- Month 3\\u20134: Continue vendor termination closures; issue co-working RFP and consolidate 8 operators to preferred panel of 1\\u20132\\n- Month 4\\u20136: Execute final Salesforce contract amendment; complete co-working consolidation and migrate headcount to retained locations\\n- Month 6+: Institutionalise quarterly vendor governance reviews; enforce category ownership to prevent tail-spend creep\\n\\n6. RISKS AND MITIGATIONS\\n- Salesforce service disruption: Negotiate phased licence reduction with no-downtime SLA protection\\n- Departmental resistance to terminations: Engage budget owners early to pre-empt escalations\\n- Co-working lease break penalties: Review break clauses before issuing termination notices\\n\\nRecommended next step: Assign procurement lead to initiate Salesforce UK renegotiation by 30 April 2026, while simultaneously activating the 265-vendor termination program in Week 1 to capture quick-win savings in parallel.\";\n\nconst cellAddr = XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r: 2, c: 0}); // A3 (0-indexed: row 2, col 0)\nconsole.log('Writing to cell:', cellAddr);\n\nws[cellAddr] = { t: 's', v: memoText };\n\n// Update sheet range if needed\nconst range = XLSX.utils.decode_range(ws['!ref'] || 'A1:A1');\nif (range.e.r < 2) range.e.r = 2;\nws['!ref'] = XLSX.utils.encode_range(range);\n\n// Write back\nXLSX.writeFile(wb, filePath);\nconsole.log('Done. File saved.');\n\n// Verify\nconst wb2 = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\nconst ws2 = wb2.Sheets['CEOCFO Recommendations'];\nconsole.log('\\nVerification:');\nconsole.log('A1 still exists:', !!ws2['A1']);\nconsole.log('A2 still:', ws2['A2'] ? ws2['A2'].v : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A3 first 200 chars:', ws2['A3'] ? ws2['A3'].v.substring(0, 200) : '(empty)');\n```\n\nSave as write_memo.js in C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/ and run with node. Return the complete output including verification results.","agentId":"a454257785fed0dc5","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The script ran successfully. Here is the complete output:\n\n```\nA1 exists: true\nA2 exists: true\nA1 value preview: Please prepare a short memo (maximum 1 page) summarizing your findings and recom\nA2 value: CEOCFORecommendations\nWriting to cell: A3\nDone. File saved.\n\nVerification:\nA1 still exists: true\nA2 still: CEOCFORecommendations\nA3 first 200 chars: MEMORANDUM\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Procurement & Finance\nDATE: 23 March 2026\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\n\n1. VENDO\n```\n\nKey results:\n\n- A1 and A2 were untouched — A1 holds the template instruction text, A2 holds the label \"CEOCFORecommendations\".\n- `XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r: 2, c: 0})` correctly resolved to `A3`.\n- The full memo was written to A3 and verified on re-read, with the opening 200 characters confirming the correct content starts with \"MEMORANDUM\\nTO: Chief Executive Officer...\".\n- The workbook was saved back to `/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx`."}],"totalDurationMs":56781,"totalTokens":17322,"totalToolUseCount":6,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":276,"cache_read_input_tokens":16702,"output_tokens":343,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":276},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017CCKAQWgTavUTYb93aQC5s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"STEP 12 is complete. The memo has been written to **A3** of the `CEOCFO Recommendations` sheet. A1 and A2 are untouched.\n\nHere's what was written:\n\n---\n\n**MEMORANDUM**\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Procurement & Finance\nDATE: 23 March 2026\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\n\n**1. VENDOR SPEND OVERVIEW**\n- 386 active vendors | Total LTM spend: $7.89M\n- Breakdown: 265 vendors for Termination ($1.48M, 18.7%); 22 for Optimisation ($4.90M, 62.1%); 99 for Consolidation ($1.51M, 19.2%)\n- Top 10 vendors account for 63.9% of total spend — acute concentration risk\n\n**3. TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES**\n- Opportunities structured across Immediate and Parallel Strategic tracks to maximise speed, feasibility, and minimise operational risk\n- Salesforce UK Contract Renegotiation (Immediate): right-size licences and secure multi-year pricing — est. $467,584\n- Long-tail Vendor Termination Program (Parallel Strategic): cancel 265 Terminate-rated vendors, prioritising Score-1 SaaS first — est. $163,215\n- Co-working & Office Space Consolidation: rationalise 8 vendors ($828K portfolio) to 1–2 preferred operators — est. $124,175\nTotal estimated savings: $754,974\n\n**4. ESTIMATED SAVINGS SUMMARY**\n- Total identified savings: $754,974 (9.6% of total LTM spend)\n- Year 1 conservatively realisable: $453,000 (60% of identified savings)\n- Payback on implementation effort: under 6 months\n\n**5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP**\n- Month 1–2: Launch Salesforce renegotiation with procurement lead; activate 265-vendor termination program targeting Score-1 SaaS cancellations first\n- Month 3–4: Continue vendor termination closures; issue co-working RFP and consolidate 8 operators to preferred panel of 1–2\n- Month 4–6: Execute final Salesforce contract amendment; complete co-working consolidation and migrate headcount to retained locations\n- Month 6+: Institutionalise quarterly vendor governance reviews; enforce category ownership to prevent tail-spend creep\n\n**6. RISKS AND MITIGATIONS**\n- Salesforce service disruption: Negotiate phased licence reduction with no-downtime SLA protection\n- Departmental resistance to terminations: Engage budget owners early to pre-empt escalations\n- Co-working lease break penalties: Review break clauses before issuing termination notices\n\nRecommended next step: Assign procurement lead to initiate Salesforce UK renegotiation by 30 April 2026, while simultaneously activating the 265-vendor termination program in Week 1 to capture quick-win savings in parallel.\n\n---\n\nNote: The template (A1) asks for a **Google Doc link** to be added below the memo — you'll need to paste that manually once you've created the Google Doc version."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5287,"cache_read_input_tokens":23364,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5287,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2abd3ed-573c-41f0-9505-cb2e0fcd9d65","uuid":"1298752f-1fd4-4fc3-8a60-d18d3a075f9b"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":588651,"duration_api_ms":581140,"num_turns":5,"result":"STEP 12 is complete. The memo has been written to **A3** of the `CEOCFO Recommendations` sheet. A1 and A2 are untouched.\n\nHere's what was written:\n\n---\n\n**MEMORANDUM**\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Procurement & Finance\nDATE: 23 March 2026\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\n\n**1. VENDOR SPEND OVERVIEW**\n- 386 active vendors | Total LTM spend: $7.89M\n- Breakdown: 265 vendors for Termination ($1.48M, 18.7%); 22 for Optimisation ($4.90M, 62.1%); 99 for Consolidation ($1.51M, 19.2%)\n- Top 10 vendors account for 63.9% of total spend — acute concentration risk\n\n**3. TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES**\n- Opportunities structured across Immediate and Parallel Strategic tracks to maximise speed, feasibility, and minimise operational risk\n- Salesforce UK Contract Renegotiation (Immediate): right-size licences and secure multi-year pricing — est. $467,584\n- Long-tail Vendor Termination Program (Parallel Strategic): cancel 265 Terminate-rated vendors, prioritising Score-1 SaaS first — est. $163,215\n- Co-working & Office Space Consolidation: rationalise 8 vendors ($828K portfolio) to 1–2 preferred operators — est. $124,175\nTotal estimated savings: $754,974\n\n**4. ESTIMATED SAVINGS SUMMARY**\n- Total identified savings: $754,974 (9.6% of total LTM spend)\n- Year 1 conservatively realisable: $453,000 (60% of identified savings)\n- Payback on implementation effort: under 6 months\n\n**5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP**\n- Month 1–2: Launch Salesforce renegotiation with procurement lead; activate 265-vendor termination program targeting Score-1 SaaS cancellations first\n- Month 3–4: Continue vendor termination closures; issue co-working RFP and consolidate 8 operators to preferred panel of 1–2\n- Month 4–6: Execute final Salesforce contract amendment; complete co-working consolidation and migrate headcount to retained locations\n- Month 6+: Institutionalise quarterly vendor governance reviews; enforce category ownership to prevent tail-spend creep\n\n**6. RISKS AND MITIGATIONS**\n- Salesforce service disruption: Negotiate phased licence reduction with no-downtime SLA protection\n- Departmental resistance to terminations: Engage budget owners early to pre-empt escalations\n- Co-working lease break penalties: Review break clauses before issuing termination notices\n\nRecommended next step: Assign procurement lead to initiate Salesforce UK renegotiation by 30 April 2026, while simultaneously activating the 265-vendor termination program in Week 1 to capture quick-win savings in parallel.\n\n---\n\nNote: The template (A1) asks for a **Google Doc link** to be added below the memo — you'll need to paste that manually once you've created the Google Doc version.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d2abd3ed-573c-41f0-9505-cb2e0fcd9d65","total_cost_usd":1.0472115,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":33045,"cache_read_input_tokens":74851,"output_tokens":10101,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":33045},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":39,"outputTokens":36305,"cacheReadInputTokens":384140,"cacheCreationInputTokens":103274,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.0472115,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_0129ZD4ysJvWVRu9mo93Bebf","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/temp_check.js","content":"const XLSX = require('xlsx');\nconst path = 'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx';\nconst wb = XLSX.readFile(path);\n\n// Get unique suggestion values\nconsole.log('=== UNIQUE SUGGESTION VALUES ===');\nconst vaa = wb.Sheets['Vendor Analysis Assessment'];\nconst vaaData = XLSX.utils.sheet_to_json(vaa, {defval: ''});\nconst suggMap = {};\nvaaData.forEach(row => {\n  const s = row['Suggestions (Consolidate / Terminate / Optimize costs)'] || '(blank)';\n  if (!suggMap[s]) suggMap[s] = {count: 0, spend: 0};\n  suggMap[s].count++;\n  suggMap[s].spend += parseFloat(row['Last 12 months Cost (USD)']) || 0;\n});\nObject.entries(suggMap).forEach(([k,v]) => {\n  console.log(`\"${k}\": count=${v.count}, spend=${v.spend.toFixed(2)}`);\n});\n\n// Get A1 from Top 3 Opportunities\nconsole.log('\\n=== TOP 3 OPP A1 ===');\nconst t3 = wb.Sheets['Top 3 Opportunities'];\nif (t3['A1']) console.log('A1:', JSON.stringify(t3['A1'].v));\n\n// Get A1, A2 from CEOCFO Recommendations\nconsole.log('\\n=== CEOCFO A1, A2 ===');\nconst ceo = wb.Sheets['CEOCFO Recommendations'];\nif (ceo['A1']) console.log('A1:', JSON.stringify(ceo['A1'].v));\nif (ceo['A2']) console.log('A2:', JSON.stringify(ceo['A2'].v));\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01LN2wKCkcn5W6QkwB5NdTiS","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/write_memo.js","content":"const XLSX = require('xlsx');\nconst filePath = 'C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx';\n\nconst wb = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\nconst sheetName = 'CEOCFO Recommendations';\nconst ws = wb.Sheets[sheetName];\n\n// Verify A1 and A2 are present (do not overwrite)\nconsole.log('A1 exists:', !!ws['A1']);\nconsole.log('A2 exists:', !!ws['A2']);\nconsole.log('A1 value preview:', ws['A1'] ? ws['A1'].v.substring(0, 80) : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A2 value:', ws['A2'] ? ws['A2'].v : '(empty)');\n\n// Write only to A3\nconst memoText = \"MEMORANDUM\\nTO: Chief Executive Officer | Chief Financial Officer\\nFROM: R. Jegadeswari, Procurement & Finance\\nDATE: 23 March 2026\\nRE: Vendor Spend Rationalisation — Findings & Recommendations\\n\\n1. VENDOR SPEND OVERVIEW\\n- 386 active vendors | Total LTM spend: $7.89M\\n- Breakdown: 265 vendors for Termination ($1.48M, 18.7%); 22 for Optimisation ($4.90M, 62.1%); 99 for Consolidation ($1.51M, 19.2%)\\n- Top 10 vendors account for 63.9% of total spend — acute concentration risk\\n\\n3. TOP 3 OPPORTUNITIES\\n- Opportunities structured across Immediate and Parallel Strategic tracks to maximise speed, feasibility, and minimise operational risk\\n- Salesforce UK Contract Renegotiation (Immediate): right-size licences and secure multi-year pricing — est. $467,584\\n- Long-tail Vendor Termination Program (Parallel Strategic): cancel 265 Terminate-rated vendors, prioritising Score-1 SaaS first — est. $163,215\\n- Co-working & Office Space Consolidation: rationalise 8 vendors ($828K portfolio) to 1\\u20132 preferred operators — est. $124,175\\nTotal estimated savings: $754,974\\n\\n4. ESTIMATED SAVINGS SUMMARY\\n- Total identified savings: $754,974 (9.6% of total LTM spend)\\n- Year 1 conservatively realisable: $453,000 (60% of identified savings)\\n- Payback on implementation effort: under 6 months\\n\\n5. IMPLEMENTATION ROADMAP\\n- Month 1\\u20132: Launch Salesforce renegotiation with procurement lead; activate 265-vendor termination program targeting Score-1 SaaS cancellations first\\n- Month 3\\u20134: Continue vendor termination closures; issue co-working RFP and consolidate 8 operators to preferred panel of 1\\u20132\\n- Month 4\\u20136: Execute final Salesforce contract amendment; complete co-working consolidation and migrate headcount to retained locations\\n- Month 6+: Institutionalise quarterly vendor governance reviews; enforce category ownership to prevent tail-spend creep\\n\\n6. RISKS AND MITIGATIONS\\n- Salesforce service disruption: Negotiate phased licence reduction with no-downtime SLA protection\\n- Departmental resistance to terminations: Engage budget owners early to pre-empt escalations\\n- Co-working lease break penalties: Review break clauses before issuing termination notices\\n\\nRecommended next step: Assign procurement lead to initiate Salesforce UK renegotiation by 30 April 2026, while simultaneously activating the 265-vendor termination program in Week 1 to capture quick-win savings in parallel.\";\n\nconst cellAddr = XLSX.utils.encode_cell({r: 2, c: 0}); // A3 (0-indexed: row 2, col 0)\nconsole.log('Writing to cell:', cellAddr);\n\nws[cellAddr] = { t: 's', v: memoText };\n\n// Update sheet range if needed\nconst range = XLSX.utils.decode_range(ws['!ref'] || 'A1:A1');\nif (range.e.r < 2) range.e.r = 2;\nws['!ref'] = XLSX.utils.encode_range(range);\n\n// Write back\nXLSX.writeFile(wb, filePath);\nconsole.log('Done. File saved.');\n\n// Verify\nconst wb2 = XLSX.readFile(filePath);\nconst ws2 = wb2.Sheets['CEOCFO Recommendations'];\nconsole.log('\\nVerification:');\nconsole.log('A1 still exists:', !!ws2['A1']);\nconsole.log('A2 still:', ws2['A2'] ? ws2['A2'].v : '(empty)');\nconsole.log('A3 first 200 chars:', ws2['A3'] ? ws2['A3'].v.substring(0, 200) : '(empty)');\n"}}],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"cee61f51-7f66-442d-bc97-2c6926eebfc1"}
